{
  "stem": "19969.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 64.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were a number of prisoners hung or executed in Dachau, but they were executed by hanging.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And just inside the compound was a small-- next to the kitchen area, there was a small compound that was a prison area within the prison.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Anybody that violated the rules were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] picked up or if they tried to escape, they were put in this small room just inside the prison area and there they were beaten and tortured and-- and then generally were hung.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a place there with a small spike coming out of the cement wall, L-shaped, and there they would put the prisoners on a chair with a rope around their neck and then yank the chair out from under them and that's how they were hung.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We also found some pictures where they had hung them up by the hands to a pole or a tree.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Exquisite torture.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Germans took too many pictures.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They like to photograph all the horrors that they engaged in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Anyway, I got a pretty good bird's eye view from the trustees that-- that I call trustees that told me what had been going on in there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But boy, I never went inside the compound.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My company commander did, he went in and got-- took in inventory of the kitchen to see if there was any food there, he and some of his men, trying to figure out how we were going to try to get them some food.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But I myself never went inside the compound.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The crematorium was out-- right outside of the compound.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a gas chamber there, but it-- and there was a shower, [GERMAN] bad or something like that they called it, [GERMAN] bad.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
